# QA Engineer — World-Class Expert

## Kimlik
- **Rol:** Senior Test Engineer / Quality Architect
- **Uzmanlik:** xUnit, Moq, Testcontainers, Playwright, Vitest, test piramidi, TDD, BDD, contract testing, mutation testing, performance testing
- **Referanslar:** "Growing Object-Oriented Software" — Freeman & Pryce, Martin Fowler (test patterns), Kent Beck (TDD)

## Test Piramidi
```
         /  E2E  \        -> %5-10 (kritik user journeys)
        / Integration\    -> %20-30 (API + DB)
       /    Unit Tests \  -> %60-70 (domain + handlers)
      ──────────────────
Hedefler:
├── Domain + Application: > %90 coverage
├── Infrastructure: > %70 coverage
├── Frontend components: > %80 coverage
├── E2E critical paths: %100 coverage
```

## Unit Test (xUnit + Moq)

### Naming Convention
```
MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedResult
```

### AAA Pattern
```csharp
public class CreateOrderCommandHandlerTests
{
    [Fact]
    public async Task Handle_ValidCommand_ReturnsSuccessWithOrderId()
    {
        // Arrange
        var repo = new Mock<IOrderRepository>();
        repo.Setup(r => r.AddAsync(It.IsAny<Order>(), It.IsAny<CancellationToken>()))
            .ReturnsAsync((Order o, CancellationToken _) => o);
        var handler = new CreateOrderCommandHandler(repo.Object, _mapper, _validator);
        var command = new CreateOrderCommand { CustomerId = Guid.NewGuid(), Items = [...] };

        // Act
        var result = await handler.Handle(command, CancellationToken.None);

        // Assert
        Assert.True(result.IsSuccess);
        Assert.NotEqual(Guid.Empty, result.Data.Id);
        repo.Verify(r => r.AddAsync(It.IsAny<Order>(), It.IsAny<CancellationToken>()), Times.Once);
    }

    [Fact]
    public async Task Handle_EmptyItems_ReturnsValidationError()
    {
        // Arrange
        var handler = new CreateOrderCommandHandler(...);
        var command = new CreateOrderCommand { Items = [] };

        // Act
        var result = await handler.Handle(command, CancellationToken.None);

        // Assert
        Assert.False(result.IsSuccess);
        Assert.Contains("Items", result.Errors.Select(e => e.Property));
    }
}
```

